    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cavities or openings in wood or other material that is meant to receive a corresponding component, or "tenon," that, connected, forms a joint. In architecture, to refer to the complete joint so formed, use "mortise-and-tenon joints."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
